# GitHub Copilot SDK - AKS Monitor Agent

> **An intelligent AI agent that monitors Azure Kubernetes Service clusters and reports issues to GitHub**

Built with the [GitHub Copilot SDK](https://github.com/github/copilot-sdk), this project demonstrates how to create production-ready AI agents that integrate with multiple systems using Model Context Protocol (MCP) servers.

## 🌟 Highlights

- 🤖 **AI-Powered**: Uses GitHub Copilot SDK with GPT-4o
- 🔗 **Multi-System Integration**: GitHub + Azure + AKS via MCP servers
- 💬 **Interactive**: Conversational interface with step-by-step guidance
- 🔍 **Comprehensive**: Monitors nodes, pods, services, and resources
- 📝 **Automated**: Creates detailed GitHub issues automatically
- 🎯 **Production-Ready**: Error handling, state management, and user confirmations

## 🚀 Quick Start

```bash
# Install dependencies
npm install

# Run the AKS Monitor Agent (no additional setup needed!)
npm run aks-monitor
```

Then follow the interactive prompts to:
1. Authenticate with Azure (tenant ID, subscription ID)
2. Connect to your AKS cluster (cluster name, resource group)
3. Run diagnostics and review findings
4. Create GitHub issues for problems found

